                '_ar_code_meaning'   => "Viking Professional dishwashers are equipped with an overflow protection system in the base pan below the wash tub. When water accumulates in the base pan — from an internal leak, a failed sump seal, or an overfill condition — a float switch in the base pan activates, triggering an automatic shutdown and drain cycle to prevent water from reaching the floor.\n\nWhen the overflow protection triggers, the dishwasher will display an error code (model-dependent), stop the wash cycle, and attempt to drain. The underlying cause of the water accumulation must be identified and repaired before the dishwasher can be returned to service.",
                '_ar_causes'         => [['title' => 'Internal Sump or Hose Leak', 'description' => 'A failed sump seal, cracked spray arm, or loose hose connection inside the dishwasher tub is allowing wash water to leak into the base pan.'], ['title' => 'Door Gasket Leak Reaching Base Pan', 'description' => 'A deteriorated door gasket allows wash water to spray out the door area during operation, running into the base pan below.'], ['title' => 'Float Switch Stuck in Activated Position', 'description' => 'Foam from excessive or incorrect detergent, or a small piece of debris, has lifted the base pan float and is holding it in the triggered position even with no water present.']],
                '_ar_diy_steps'      => [['title' => 'Check for Detergent Foam', 'description' => 'If the overflow protection triggered immediately after using a new detergent or too much detergent, foam may have lifted the base float. Remove the dishwasher lower kick panel and look for foam or water in the base pan. If foam is present, wait for it to dissipate.'], ['title' => 'Tilt the Dishwasher', 'description' => 'With the dishwasher unplugged, carefully tilt it forward 45 degrees to drain any accumulated water from the base pan. This may clear the float trigger and allow the dishwasher to restart — but the underlying leak source must still be identified.']],
                '_ar_when_to_call'   => 'The base pan overflow protection system protects against water damage to the floor. Once triggered, the leak source must be professionally identified and repaired. Do not continue using the dishwasher until the cause of base pan water accumulation has been resolved.',
                '_ar_cost_range'     => '$130 – $420',
                '_ar_severity'       => 'High',
                '_ar_faqs'           => [['question' => 'My Viking dishwasher shows a water error and will not run — what does this mean?', 'answer' => 'A water-related error code combined with the dishwasher refusing to run or running only the drain cycle typically means the overflow protection system has been triggered. Water has accumulated in the base pan below the wash tub. This may be caused by a leak inside the dishwasher, an overfill condition, or foam from incorrect detergent. Schedule professional service to identify and repair the leak source before continuing use.']]]],

    ];
}

