                '_ar_severity'       => 'High',
                '_ar_faqs'           => [['question' => 'My Viking hood fan only runs at high speed and I cannot change the speed — is this the control board?', 'answer' => 'A fan that defaults to high speed with no speed adjustment is a common control board triac failure. The triac that modulates motor speed for the low and medium settings has failed in the full-on state, while the motor itself continues to run at maximum speed. Control board replacement restores full speed control. Do not operate the hood continuously at high speed as this accelerates motor wear.']]]],

